{"id":"math120-critical_pt120-003","cid":"MATH 120","topic":"Applications of Derivatives","subtopic":"Optimization","difficulty":2,"license":"CC BY-NC-SA (Numberbender original)","instruction":"A ball is thrown upward. Its height is h(t) = {a}t^2 + {b}t + {c} feet. Find the time t at which it reaches maximum height, then find that maximum height.","params":{"a":{"type":"int","min":-16,"max":-8},"b":{"type":"int","min":20,"max":60},"c":{"type":"int","min":0,"max":10}},"answer_expr":"critical_pt120","steps":["h'(t) = {two_a}t + {b}. Set h'(t) = 0.","t = {x_star} seconds.","Maximum height = h({x_star}) = {fx_star} feet."],"tags":["survey-calculus","optimization","projectile","maximum"]}
